<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 6:26PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL SCHUYLKILL AND
SOUTHEASTERN COLUMBIA COUNTIES THROUGH 715 PM EDT...
At 625 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Shenandoah, moving south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Pottsville, Shenandoah, Minersville, Mahanoy City, Frackville, St.
Clair, Ashland, Port Carbon, Girardville, Friedensburg, Lavelle,
Marlin, Altamont, Englewood, Forrestville, Branchdale, Seltzer,
Aristes, Fountain Springs and Heckscherville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
